org.forgerock.openam.cts.monitoring

Interface CTSOperationsMonitoringStore

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CTSMonitoringStoreImpl

    public interface CTSOperationsMonitoringStore
    A data structure for storing monitoring information about CTS operations.
    The CTS will use an instance of this data structure to store information about operations as and when they occur and then the CTS monitoring framework will us the same instance to pull information out to send to clients as monitoring requests are made.
    Since:
    12.0.0

    • Method Detail

      • addTokenOperation

        void addTokenOperation(Token token,
                       CTSOperation operation,
                       boolean success)
        Adds a Token operation into the monitoring store.
        The operation is mapped to the type of the token. The operations per configurable period and cumulative count will be updated for the token type and operation.
        Passing in null as the token will mean that the operation is not mapped to a particular token type, this is for operations such as delete and list as the type of token cannot be determined. The operations per configurable period and cumulative count will be updated for the operation.
        Parameters:
        token - The Token the operation was performed on.
        operation - The operation performed.
        success - Whether the operation was successful or not.

      • getAverageOperationsPerPeriod

        double getAverageOperationsPerPeriod(TokenType type,
                                     CTSOperation operation)
        Gets the average rate of operations made in a given period.
        Will return the number of the specified operation made on the specified type token in a given (configurable) period.
        Passing in null as the operation will mean that the method will return the number of the specified operation made on tokens, which the type cannot be determined, i.e. Delete and List operations.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of token to get the operation average rate for.
        operation - The operation to get the average rate for.
        Returns:
        The average number of operations made on the type token in a given period.

      • getOperationsCumulativeCount

        long getOperationsCumulativeCount(TokenType type,
                                  CTSOperation operation)
        Gets the cumulative count of operations made since server start up.
        Will return the total number of the specified operation made on the specified type of token since the server stared.
        Passing in null as the operation will mean that the method will return the total number of the specified operation made on tokens, which the type cannot be determined, i.e. Delete and List operations.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of token to get the cumulative count for.
        operation - The operation to get the cumulative count for.
        Returns:
        The total number of operations made on the type of token since server start up.

      • getOperationFailuresCumulativeCount

        long getOperationFailuresCumulativeCount(CTSOperation operation)
        Gets the cumulative count of failures of this operation type since server startup.
        Note that failure counts are not distinguished by token type as in most failure cases this information is not available.
        Parameters:
        operation - The operation to get the failure count for.
        Returns:
        The total number of failed operations of this type since server startup.
